<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch-structure" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Book Structure</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>A publishing framework should be easy to navigate. This chapter explains the basic organization of the project so that authors can find the files they need quickly.</p>
  </introduction>

  <section xml:id="sec-files-and-folders">
    <title>Files and folders</title>
    <p>The top-level structure is intentionally simple:</p>
    <itemizedlist>
      <item><p><code>chapters/</code> holds the main content.</p></item>
      <item><p><code>frontmatter/</code> stores title and metadata files.</p></item>
      <item><p><code>templates/</code> contains reusable layout patterns.</p></item>
      <item><p><code>output/</code> is generated by the build process.</p></item>
    </itemizedlist>
    <p>Keeping these areas separate makes it easier to maintain the project over time.</p>
  </section>
</chapter>
